The paper discusses the anonymization of location data in location-based services, which is a topic related to privacy and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the utility of the obfuscation mechanisms for both users and data analysts, which is related to data management and analysis (cs.DB). The paper introduces the notion of asymptotic anonymity, which is related to statistical learning and analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the optimal geo-indistinguishable mechanism, which is related to information theory and cryptography (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses empirical analysis to compare different obfuscation mechanisms, which is related to data mining and machine learning (cs.SI).
